    <h2>Educational Content Only</h2>
    <p>The Retiree Report is an educational resource. All articles, guides, comparisons, and other content published
      on this site are intended to help you understand Medicare — not to serve as personalized insurance advice.</p>
    <p>Nothing on this site should be construed as a recommendation to enroll in any specific Medicare plan,
      insurance product, or healthcare program.</p>

    <h2>Not a Substitute for Professional Advice</h2>
    <p>Medicare is complex, and the right choice depends on your individual health needs, budget, prescription
      drugs, preferred doctors, and location. The information on this site is general in nature and may not apply to
      your specific situation.</p>
    <p>Before making any Medicare enrollment decision, you should speak with a licensed Medicare insurance agent or
      advisor who can review your personal circumstances.</p>

    <h2>Licensing</h2>
    <p>The agent behind The Retiree Report is licensed to sell Medicare insurance products in North Carolina and
      South Carolina only. If you are located outside of NC or SC, this site can still serve as an educational
      resource, but we cannot provide licensed insurance guidance for your state.</p>

    <h2>Accuracy of Information</h2>
    <p>We work hard to keep the information on this site accurate and up to date. However, Medicare rules, plan
      details, premiums, and coverage change regularly — often annually. Always verify current information with <a
        href="https://www.medicare.gov" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Medicare.gov</a> or a licensed
      agent before making enrollment decisions.</p>
    <p>We are not affiliated with Medicare, the Centers for Medicare &amp; Medicaid Services (CMS), or any
      government agency.</p>

    <h2>No Carrier Affiliation</h2>
    <p>The Retiree Report is independently operated. Mentions of specific insurance carriers, plan types, or
      Medicare products are for educational purposes only and do not constitute an endorsement. We work with
      multiple carriers and our goal is to find the right fit for you — not to push any particular product.</p>

    <h2>External Links</h2>
    <p>This site may link to external websites, including Medicare.gov, Social Security Administration, and other
      government or educational resources. We are not responsible for the accuracy or content of those sites.</p>

    <h2>No Guarantee of Results</h2>
    <p>Every person's Medicare situation is different. Information shared on this site, in our newsletter, or in
      individual conversations reflects general knowledge and experience — it is not a guarantee of specific
      outcomes, savings, or coverage.</p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>If you have questions about this disclaimer or want to speak with a licensed agent, visit the <a
        href="/pages/work-with-me.html">Work With Me</a> page.</p>

